{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 40°C, or the lowest temperature setting on your oven. Line a baking tray with baking paper and set aside.","Place lemon zest into mixing bowl and grate <b>20 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer onto prepared baking tray and spread out evenly into a thin layer. Place into oven and dehydrate for 80-90 minutes (40°C) or until zest is completely dry. Rinse and dry mixing bowl.","Place peppercorns, salt and dried zest into mixing bowl and blend <b>6 sec\/speed 10<b>, until well combined. Transfer into a sealable container and store in a cool, dark place until ready to use."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 - 6 lemons, zest only, no white pith","60 g whole black peppercorns","130 g Himalayan salt"]}],"id":"r152078","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-Ikg1BrLlQus\/XZXYa_VhI6I\/AAAAAAAAf-w\/gizKctGv8k84pV-t9A4UDQaHws1BJYf9wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Nk-ubH80TzzqQhWg.png","title":"Lemon pepper seasoning","publishedAt":"2018-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0.2 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"0.6 g","calories":"17 kJ \/ 4 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, sealable container, baking tray, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This seasoning can be kept in a sealable container in the pantry for up to 6 months.","If your oven temperature doesn't go all the way down to 40°C, try using a dehydrator.","This seasoning is great on fish, chicken, vegetables or roasted legumes (such as chickpeas)."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","1h 35m","43 portions"]}